abstract.para: The Cooperative Lakes Monitoring Program (CLMP) has been an important component of Michigan's inland lakes monitoring program for over 39 years, which makes it the second oldest volunteer monitoring program for lakes in the country. The primary purpose of this cooperative program is to help citizen volunteers monitor indicators of water quality in their lake and document changes in lake quality over time. The goals of the CLMP are: Provide baseline information and document trends in water quality for individual lakes, Educate lake residents, users and interested citizens in the collection of water quality data, lake ecology and lake management practices, provide a cost-effective process for the DEQ to increase baseline data for lakes state-wide. Since 1992, the Michigan Lake and Stream Associations (MLSA) has administered the CLMP jointly with the Michigan Department of Environmental Quality (DEQ) under a Memorandum of Understanding. The ML&SA will continue to administer this program under the Michigan Clean Water Corps

section.title: Secchi depth
section.para: Secchi: At least 8 measurements are taken, relatively evenly spaced between May 13 and September 15

section.title: Total phosphorus
section.para: Total phosphorus was measured from water samples. One surface grab sample was taken 7-10 days after ice-out (typically April or May) when lake is mixed and 1 surface grab sample in late summer/early fall (typically August or September) when lake is stratified.
1998-2007 collected replicate samples (4 TP values per sampling event)

section.title: Chlorophyll a
section.para: Chlorophyll a was measured from water samples. Five sampling events (May-September), depth-integrated sample. Sample preserved with MgCO3, filtered in the field, stored in freezer.
1998-2007 collected replicate samples (R2 between chl of sample and replicate=0.97) and had DEQ collect sample with volunteer (R2 between chl of sample and DEQ replicate=0.89)

section.title: QA/QC
section.para: General QA/QC for data entry: quality assurance program plan for each MiCorps member program before data can be entered, common data entry errors flagged, data reviewed by MiCorps staff

samplingDescription.para: Sampling regime depends on the parameter of interest. Secchi transparency - 8 measurements relatively evenly spaced between May 13 and September 15.Total phosphorus - surface grab sample 7-10 days after ice-out (typically April or May) when lake is mixed and 1 surface grab sample in late summer/early fall (typically August or September) when lake is stratified. Chlorophyll a - 5 sampling events (May-September), depth-integrated sample. Sample preserved with MgCO3, filtered in the field, stored in freezer
